hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I read a lot noprescription-rx.com reviews A nocturnal finish on the Beautiful Boulevard which feels like one of those Friday night Six Nations games: great for TV, not so great for the travelling support. Given the cobbles on the Champs, it will be dire if it rains. Cavendish will have spent seven stages battling for survival from Lyon over the Ventoux and points north with this one stage in mind, so a fifth consecutive victory here would be richly deserved. Barring an act of God it's hard not to see him winning.
